Anyway, god bless @Folkroom, they'll find a new place and build a new community and it'll be great. I hope I get to play there at some point in the future.

It seems the people who run The Harrison now are more committed to operating in "the Metaverse" at the expense of preserving and nurturing the really fucking great thing they had. Call me a luddite but: what a stupid thing that is.
We did our first @YeahGreyhounds headline show there! @MassiveDad told jokes before us! @kitlochery compered! It was one of the most fun nights I've ever played!

And the room itself was perfect. 30 people made it feel packed. The bar was upstairs so everyone downstairs listened. It could be rowdy and it could be pindrop quiet, and it was fun both ways. I opened shows there, I headlined there, I hosted there. And the beer was nice too

@Folkroom In all seriousness, one of the things I always wanted from living in London as a musical community and Folkroom and The Harrison facilitated that. I met @joeinnes, Oh Sister, @winterfalle, @iamdanduke, @WorryDolls, @patchandgiant, @40elephantgang and so many other amazing people

Tonight in London it's the end of an era, as @Folkroom plays its last ever gig at The Harrison in King's Cross, a place I loved playing if only because it read as: Harry Harris at The Harrison on Harrison Street.
